Sentencas: Porous copper/yttria-stabilized zirconia (Cu/YSZ) thin tapes were produced to be used as anodes in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFC).
Titulo: Porous Cu/YSZ anodes processed by aqueous tape casting for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The use of copper in these cermets promises a better chemical resistance and a lower operating temperature for SOFC.
Titulo: Porous Cu/YSZ anodes processed by aqueous tape casting for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: Graphite and cassava starch were used as pore forming agents, which led to porosity values between 30 and 40%.
Titulo: Porous Cu/YSZ anodes processed by aqueous tape casting for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: Tapes were obtained by aqueous tape casting with controlled thickness (300-2000 mu m).
Titulo: Porous Cu/YSZ anodes processed by aqueous tape casting for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: Before casting, CuO/YSZ aqueous suspensions were formulated based on rheological characterization.
Titulo: Porous Cu/YSZ anodes processed by aqueous tape casting for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: Sintering was carried out at 1150 degrees C during 1 h. Cu/YSZ tapes were obtained after redox reaction, performed at 400, 600 and 800 degrees C. (C) 2017
Titulo: Porous Cu/YSZ anodes processed by aqueous tape casting for IT-SOFC
